Open design questions (defer to user)
------------------------------------
- Do you want `AppController` to be the owner of `TrackingProgressDialog` (so UI only connects to controller signals), or have MainWindow keep the dialog and just use controller signals? -- User said MainWindow should keep owning it. We'll follow that.
- Should `AppController` expose storage pointer directly or only via controlled accessors? Expose pointer via `trackingDataStorage()` is convenient for existing code, but consider accessor methods for read-only operations to maintain encapsulation.

Notes about meta-types
----------------------
- `TrackingManager::registerMetaTypes()` exists; ensure that if AppController forwards types via signals (e.g., `Tracking::AllWormTracks`), those meta-types are registered before connections cross threads. `TrackingManager` registers them on construction but AppController should either call the same registration or rely on TrackingManager to register them.

